                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Paris"
                    },
                    "body": "I guess the spec is incorrect or obsolete, since at least in the C++ (and Python) implementation arrays a 64-bit length (signed, but it doesn't matter much).\r\n\r\nThe 32-bit limitation does apply to the underlying data of list arrays (and therefore also string and binary arrays).",
